  "prompt": "What should I gift to my teacher?",
  "response": "Choosing a thoughtful gift for your teacher can show your appreciation for their hard work and dedication. Here are some ideas:\n\n1. **Personalized Items**: Consider a personalized mug, notebook, or tote bag with their name or a meaningful quote.\n\n2. **Gift Cards**: A gift card to a local coffee shop, bookstore, or office supply store allows them to choose something they truly want or need.\n\n3. **Books**: If you know their interests, a book in a genre they enjoy or a professional development book can be a great gift.\n\n4. **Stationery**: High-quality pens, notebooks, or planners can be useful for teachers.\n\n5. **Plants**: A small desk plant or succulent can brighten up their classroom or office.\n\n6. **Homemade Treats**: Baking cookies or other treats can be a heartfelt and delicious gift.\n\n7. **Classroom Supplies**: Contributing to their classroom with supplies like markers, paper, or educational games can be very helpful.\n\n8. **Thank You Card**: A handwritten note expressing your gratitude can be meaningful and appreciated.\n\n9. **Self-Care Items**: Consider candles, bath products, or a cozy blanket to help them relax.\n\n10. **Experience Gifts**: If possible, consider tickets to a local event, museum, or a gift certificate for a fun activity.\n\nRemember to consider your teacher's preferences and interests when selecting a gift!",
